## Risks

1. **Pre-existing `cognicode-mcp-server --features postgres` is broken on baseline.**
   The `axum::header` and `opentelemetry_prometheus::Prometheus` imports were
   unresolved before this PR (confirmed via `git stash` baseline test). The
   `/ready` route in `server.rs` will be exercised by the full HTTP server
   only when that feature is fixed. Not a blocker for this PR — the route
   code is type-correct and follows the existing `metrics_handler` pattern.

2. **Test flakiness** (pre-existing, see verification note). Not introduced
   or worsened by this PR.

3. **`HandlerContext` field change is a struct-level API change.** All callers
   using the builder pattern (`HandlerContext::builder().build()` or
   `HandlerContext::new()`) are unaffected because the builder's `build()`
   initializes the new field. Direct struct-literal construction was updated
   in the 3 sites within `handlers/mod.rs`. No external crate constructs
   `HandlerContext` via struct literal.

